    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Motif on bone china comprising formalized flowers, foliage, and peaches in blue underglaze; first introduced at Meissen in 1739, and copied extensively by other manufacturers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
